snippet.title: Java Method Parameters Tutorial
snippet.description:
Head to squarespace.com/alexlee to save 10% off your first purchase of a website or domain using code ALEXLEE

New course coming soon! Learn Java Fast launches on July 1st, 2020. Stay informed and join the waitlist: https://course.alexlorenlee.com/courses/learn-java-fast

- You can give methods variables! These are called method parameters. In java, you can add parameters to a method like this:

myMethod(int a, String b) {}

a and b can be any type of object or variable. This makes methods very flexible!

I hope you enjoyed this method parameters tutorial!
